BFN 

  [Excerpts] President Zine el Abidine Ben Ali conferred at 
Carthage Palace this morning with Prime Minister Hamed Karoui, 
who briefed him on the outcome of his recent official visit to 
Malaysia. [passage omitted] 
  The prime minister has announced that President Zine el 
Abidine Ben Ali has decided to introduce a limited reshuffle of 
the government as follows by appointing: 
  Ahmed Fria, minister of education and science; 
  Mondher Zenaidi, minister of transport; 
  Slaheddine Bouguerra, secretary of state to the minister 
of national economy, replacing Salah Hamdi; and 
  Chedli Laroussi, minister of state to the minister of 
agriculture 

